Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} and @Unsalted Butter{30%g} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Place a few @Salad Potatoes{350%g} at a time in between two #wooden spoon handles{} on a #cutting board{}. Make slices widthways at 3mm intervals, making sure not to cut the whole way through. Repeat with the remaining potatoes.

Put the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Garlic Cloves{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it.

Roast the parcel on the middle shelf of your oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In the meantime, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}. Finely chop the @Chives{1}(finely chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier).

== Garlic & Chive Butter ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the butter and chives.

Once the roasted garlic has cooled, cut the end with scissors, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}, then stir it into the chive butter. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

== Cheesy Bacon Hasselback Potatoes ==

When the potatoes have 10 mins remaining, sprinkle the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{60%g} and cheese over the potatoes and return to the oven for the remaining time.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

== Steaks ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Once hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side.

Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{} and spread over the garlic-chive butter, then cover with foil and allow the steak to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw steak. It's safe to eat when browned on the outside.

== Baby Leaf Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Balsamic Vinegar{12%ml} and @Olive Oil{50%ml}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Just before everything's ready, toss the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} through the dressing.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, transfer your steaks to your #serving plates{}. Spoon over any melted butter from the resting place.

Serve the cheesy bacon hasselback potatoes and baby leaf salad alongside.

Enjoy!